{
  "_comment": [
    "Copy to .mcp.json (gitignored) and list YOUR tenants.",
    "One server per tenant. The server name is what you and Claude will say out loud,",
    "so name it the way you talk about the tenant - 'wxcc-acme', not 'wxcc-org2'.",
    "",
    "The tenant is therefore part of every tool name (mcp__wxcc-acme__wxcc_delete), so",
    "acting on the wrong tenant requires calling a differently-named tool. There is",
    "deliberately no 'switch tenant' command - a mutable current-tenant pointer is how a",
    "delete meant for sandbox lands on production.",
    "",
    "Each profile needs its own .env.<profile> and its own `auth login`. Never copy a",
    "token file between profiles: that gives you a live credential for the WRONG tenant",
    "wearing the RIGHT name.",
    "",
    "A server with no WXCC_PROFILE uses .env + .wxcc/tokens.json. Point that at your",
    "safest tenant, so an unqualified request lands somewhere harmless."
  ],
  "mcpServers": {
    "wxcc-sandbox": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "python",
      "args": ["mcp_server.py"]
    },
    "wxcc-acme": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "python",
      "args": ["mcp_server.py"],
      "env": { "WXCC_PROFILE": "acme" }
    }
  }
}
